# FootballField Project Overview

## Architecture
This project follows a 3-tier architecture:
- **Frontend**: React/TypeScript application running on port 9001
- **Backend**: NodeJS RESTful API running on port 9002
- **Database**: MySQL database on port 3306

## Key Technologies
- **Frontend**: React, TypeScript, TailwindCSS, ShadcnUI
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express, Sequelize ORM
- **Database**: MySQL
- **Testing**: Jest, Supertest

## Directory Structure
```
FootballField/
├── frontend/         # React/TypeScript application
├── backend/          # Node.js API server
│   ├── src/          # Source code
│   │   ├── controllers/  # Request handlers
│   │   ├── models/       # Database models
│   │   ├── routes/       # API routes
│   │   ├── middleware/   # Express middleware
│   │   ├── services/     # Business logic
│   │   ├── utils/        # Utility functions
│   │   ├── config/       # Configuration files
│   │   ├── tests/        # Test suites
│   │   └── app.js        # Express application entry
│   ├── package.json      # Dependencies
│   └── server.js         # Server entry point
└── database/        # Database scripts and migrations
```

## Connection Flow
1. Frontend makes API requests to Backend on port 9002
2. Backend processes requests using business logic
3. Backend interacts with MySQL database
4. Backend returns responses to Frontend

## Running the Application
- Frontend: Port 9001
- Backend: Port 9002
- Database: MySQL on port 3306 (credentials in database config)
